cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.Distributed, cs.NI, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a new approach to enable a public parallel machine accessible for multi-users with multi-jobs running at the same time. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also likely as the paper mentions the deployment of multi-daemons of parallel processing engine with different configuration files specified for each user assigned to access the system. 
- cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses the concept of parallel machines dedicated for public use. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper mentions the development of an integrated system to fully control and monitor the whole system over the web. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the performance analysis of the Message Parsing Interface (MPI) engine.
